genresAdvancedInfo.name: taiko
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Taiko is a Japanese drumming style that is both powerful and precise. The drums used in taiko music are large and heavy, and are played with sticks called bachi. Taiko music is often used in festivals and ceremonies, and its rhythms and beats are meant to energize and inspire.
